* What is WebGL?

  WebGL is low-level Javascript API, which includes two languages: Javascript and GLSL. It is used to render 3D graphics in a web browser without the use of plug-ins.

.image pic/2/1.png

  API means user can directly use the services provided by the API, without having to know the implementation details of the service.


