We use OpenGL Language (GLSL) to write the details (Shader) above, and compile the Shader and pass it to WebGL. This part will be handled by the GPU for computation.

The GPU is slower than the CPU but can perform a large number of calculations simultaneously, unlike the CPU's line-by-line calculation method.


